    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "This 2001 Acura Integra Type R is a museum-quality example of Honda\u2019s front-wheel-drive engineering pinnacle. Under the hood, the hand-assembled B18C5 inline-four features factory-polished intake ports and high-compression pistons, delivering a visceral power band up to an 8,400 RPM redline. Power is managed via a precise, close-ratio five-speed manual transmission paired with a helical limited-slip differential for optimal corner-exit traction. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid due to factory-installed reinforcement braces, while the double-wishbone suspension retains its original geometry and bushing integrity. Every mechanical component, from the torque-sensing LSD to the four-wheel disc brakes, functions with factory precision. This is a zero-compromise, collector-grade specimen for the purist seeking an unmolested driving experience.",
